column2: The color was light green.  If lake should get more clear- I will need a longer disc cord.
Lake is getting more green as temperature gets more warm.
Water temperature rising with water becoming more discolored.
Had 1 3/4" of rain in short time on august 9th.  I feel this had an affect on clarity of lake.
Temperature of water is cooling.  Lake is getting more clear.
Lake is starting to turnover.  Light frost last night.
High wind the night before.  I feel this had an affect on clarity.
No secchi data for this date- missing page 1Assumed noon for sample time.
No data sheet sent for this date- only lab sheet- secchi measurement taken from lab sheet.
Wind and clouds developed- couldn't hold pontoon- lake does not appear to have turned over.
So windy- blown off deep hole.
Too windy to check temp deeper than 3 feet.
Some cumulus + cirrus clouds. Somewhat hazy-sun was shining
More clouds than blue sky. Quite a bit of pollen present in the lake.  more clouds than blue sky-lot of pollen present in the lake

This is the first reading after the big storm of July 1- 2011. Both of our boats were damaged and could not be used. Since we did not have a boat available there were no readings done after this date.
